title: High Net Investment in Nonfinancial Assets
description: In 2016, Timor-Leste had one of the highest net investments in nonfinancial assets, accounting for 40.29% of its GDP. This indicates a strong focus on infrastructure and capital development.

title: Significant Natural Resource Depletion
description: In 2021, Timor-Leste experienced substantial natural resources depletion, with energy and other natural resources accounting for 57.20% and 57.30% of GNI, respectively. This highlights a heavy reliance on resource extraction.

title: High Natural Gas Rents Contribution to GDP
description: Natural gas rents contributed 29.38% to Timor-Leste's GDP in 2021, showcasing the country's dependency on natural gas as a significant economic driver.

title: High Other Expenses as a Percentage of Total Expenses
description: In 2022, other expenses constituted 42.80% of Timor-Leste's total expenses, indicating a potential area for budgetary reevaluation and efficiency improvements.

title: Prevalence of Justification for Domestic Violence
description: In 2016, 62.8% of women in Timor-Leste believed a husband is justified in beating his wife if she neglects the children, reflecting deep-rooted societal norms and challenges in gender equality.

title: Lowest Quality of Public Services for Business
description: In 2024, Timor-Leste scored 3.2 in the Quality of Public Services and Transparency of Information for Business Location, indicating significant room for improvement.

title: Weak Dispute Resolution Services
description: The country's Dispute Resolution services scored 7.8 in 2024, highlighting challenges in effectively resolving business disputes.

title: Poor Financial Services Accessibility
description: With a score of 5.8 in 2024, Timor-Leste's accessibility of information in credit infrastructure is among the lowest globally.

title: Declining Export Growth
description: In 2023, Timor-Leste experienced a -59.99% growth in exports of goods and services, reflecting a significant downturn.

title: Negative Industry Growth
description: The industry sector, including construction, saw a -56.97% growth in 2023, indicating a substantial contraction.

title: Lowest Adjusted Net National Income Growth
description: In 2021, the adjusted net national income growth was -65.66%, one of the lowest globally, suggesting economic challenges.

title: Negative Inflation Rate
description: Timor-Leste recorded a -20.83% inflation rate in 2023, indicating deflationary pressures in the economy.

title: Poor Market Competition Regulations
description: The quality of regulations promoting market competition scored 22.25 in 2024, showing a need for regulatory improvements.
